##Before the outbreak, the game gobblers

Wechat media-fox

Features, for those who insist on serious reading options. Sohu News Extreme Day studio.

Kevin Wang yi-ran

Editor | Hu Daqi

"What's it called? "

"Can't say. "

The restaurant doesn't look like anything special. It's an ordinary food stall. The signboard is full of home cooked and barbecued food. In summer, there are plastic chairs outside, a lobby on the first floor and five or six private rooms on the second floor. Lin Jianan, in his early 30s, was in charge of the company's foreign business four or five years ago. Lin looked at the new dishes on the table, still quite ordinary: the cutlery was a common pot of stewed meat in southern restaurants, heated by an induction cooker; there was nothing unusual about the smell of meat, either. The LID was lifted, and the soup was Milky White, with a few splashes of oil, a clump of white and red meat, surrounded by garnishes that look like chunks of turnip. "Is not stewed meat? " Lin jian-an and company colleagues are the first time to go, each other diners are ready to move.

"have to know what kind of meat it is? " Move Chopsticks before, he can not help but be curious.

After repeated inquiries, the waiter lowered his voice: "Pork stew tiger meat. "

Lin Jian 'an was taken aback. He tasted one piece of meat and couldn't tell the difference. "You can't go in the kitchen and see if there's tiger skin, " he recalls. The Tiger wasn't on the table, and soon a "dragon" was on the table, serving two dishes: a bowl of soup and a plate of fried game with fish fillets. "It's a king snake, it's a big one, " said Lin, who was "a little shaky" as he paid for the meal. "One dragon, one tiger" cost more than 4,000 yuan. Only later did he learn the rules of these mystery restaurants: The game is for regulars, don't ask for food if you don't know it well.

Enjoying game may be what some restaurateurs see as the difference between a glutton and an ordinary eater. Xu Shu, the owner of a northern Cantonese restaurant for more than 20 years, has divided the menu into two categories: one on the table, with a pen and paper beside it for writing; and the other in his heart, only "like" can he order directly from his boss at the door of his kitchen, under the big fish bowl, the oil-stained cotton curtain was lifted, and the wire-mesh cage, dappled in the gloom, crouched down with its face close together, black and green, coiled a few times, was a snake the size of an arm. "It's very nourishing, " said Xu Shu, a Chaoshan resident who runs a family-run restaurant where game is rare and valuable. "Only for the guests who understand. "

Qin Gang, a forestry worker in Shaanxi Province, was responsible for turning over the "game tables" , but "there is a market for them and people will take risks" . From April 1 to May 31,2018, the National Forest Public Security Organ launched a special strike operation, handling more than 36,000 cases of various kinds, among which more than 77,000 heads (only) of various kinds of wild animals were confiscated, involving a sum of nearly 300 million yuan. Qin Gang worried: "The scope of game is not only the national protection of animals, even after SARS, civet cats are still eating, game has become a lot of people's Diet. "

Snake cage in Xu Shu Restaurant. Photo by Wang Yiran

"delicacies from all over the world. "

"No planes in the sky, no cars on the ground. No table on four legs, no kindred on two legs. " Veteran game eaters have a good sense of taste, but Hu couldn't taste most of it. He is 35 years old, is a medical company public relations middle-level, often receive out-of-town customers, reception guests often become a problem, "now so convenient, people want to eat fresh, have local characteristics. "

Hu Feng did not understand the game, only to see the price of vegetables, the more your customers eat the more satisfied. The winter before last, a northeast customer brought his own food and vegetables, wrapped in a thick layer of butter paper, and asked Hu Feng to arrange an acquaintance restaurant. When the meat came up, it was almost all lean. The customer put a large piece into his bowl: "don't ask, eat and guess! " Hu Feng tasted a mouthful, dry firewood hard to swallow, the other side told is venison. "At that time, people asked you, you have to say delicious, Venison that how expensive? " Hu Feng laughed, "this is to show identity, not what to eat. "

In addition to entertainment, Venison's status may stem from high prices, scarce supplies and the "never eaten" mystique. In his early years, master Huang of Ankang, Shaanxi Province, was an old hunter in the village. "We used to be tired of eating pheasants and wild pigs, but now we have a family farm, and it's more upscale. People from the big cities who come to visit still think it's a good thing, " said Master Huang, some tourists come to the village to buy, afraid to eat out, restaurants charge processing fees, some nearby villagers have also learned the propaganda: Pure Shennongjia mountain deep pollution away wild pheasant. At the peak of the tourist season, even eggs are snapped up.

Some game is a Marketing buzz delicacy. Lin, who grew up near the coast of Zhejiang Province, found the eastern star spots to be an expensive delicacy at the dinner table. "It's not about the price, it's about knowing how to eat them. " A friend in Fujian asked him to try a type of sea fish called "Tulong, " and "I've heard that the protein is particularly high, " Lin said, tuolong fish soup is very sticky, than the General Sea fish to a lot of fresh, big Tuolong fish often have no market price, is a lot of people on New Year's Day Gift "Pai Mian" , many foreign customers also come, named taste fresh.

Some people dare not touch chopsticks in the face of the local food culture. Xiao Xiao, a native of Shandong Province who went on a business trip to Yunnan, was "scared to cry" by the local specialty menu, "It's full of worms! And the 'bean worms' from my hometown, the Green Meat hoo-hoo. " He Xiang, a Quanzhou native, always recommends to his northern friends the local local frozen bamboo shoots, each time just know that there are insects inside, the other side is probably too scared to eat. The main ingredient is a kind of worm, which condenses into a brown translucent jelly after being boiled and cooled. "This is a good thing, ah! Special Tonic Body. " He Xiang feel earth bamboo shoots frozen has been the local characteristics of home-cooked dishes, not game.

"The cockroach we eat is not that kind of pest, it's water cockroach, " explains Wu Han, a 50-year-old seafood shop owner in the Luohu district of Jieyang, Guangdong Province, belong to aquatic insect, can boil soup or deep-fried, is the characteristic flavor of some areas in Guangdong. "Nourishing Yin and tonifying the kidney, but many people from other parts of the country are afraid to eat them, " Wu Han said. Dried lice can sell for more than 100 yuan a catty, and the wild ones are in short supply.

The tonic has made venison irreplaceable in the minds of some diners. Doing Business in Wuhan Xu Jing once went to a game husband and wife Shop, the store is not big, mostly repeat customers, game can be free with, a dish up, snake stewed Turtle, Friends Guarantee "absolutely unique" ; Qin Gang, an old forestry worker who has protected wildlife for many years, often makes unannounced visits to restaurants with departments such as industry and Commerce. In cities near the Daba Mountains, game restaurants are highly competitive, with unusual names and exquisitely sculpted shapes.

"You can't tell from the menu, " Qin Gang explained, "dragon and Phoenix Soup" is a wild pheasant braised with snakes, and "dragon and Tiger fighting" is a cat braised with snakes. Xu Shu, the restaurant owner, said that "Oboi captures the king" is turtle stew tiger meat, "Flying Fox Snow Mountain" is actually Fried Scorpion as the main dish. "Wild animals usually live in the mountains and eat natural food. Many people think they are good for their health even if they have no medicinal value, " Qin Gang said.

Qin Gang, a forester, attributes eating game to "having money to burn. " . The name of the deer deer in the south is Yuanhe, which means red and white wedding in some rural areas. The meat of the deer represents the wealth of the host family and respect for the guests. In the southeastern part of Shaanxi Province, the meat of the deer is also mixed in the ordinary market and becomes the "guest vegetable" of the farm family, it's a venison craze. The Forestry Department investigated and dealt with strictly, the seller is very vigilant, generally wait for the need to ask, will accost. There are also people whose tongues have been raised by baby fish, driving to Xining for a change of taste. Huang Shifu, a long-distance driver, said that the huangyu fish in Qinghai Lake, a National Class II protected animal, has been banned from fishing, but many tourists "don't care about the money, they just want to taste what it tastes like. " Huang says there are still many small restaurants near Qinghai Lake that carry the name Huangyu.

Smuggling case in Inner Mongolia: Bear's paw hidden in car tires. Image courtesy of the web

Appetite

At the other end of the game table are desperate poachers and game traders.

Daba Mountains is known as the "thousand Li ba mountain" . At the border of Shaanxi, Sichuan and Hubei provinces, the mountains are high and steep, the clouds are steep and the mountains are green, except for poachers and foresters, few people in this wildlife paradise can distinguish between a few unremarkable wires, buried in tree branches and leaves, hidden from view by electric generators, common as vines by day, and a switch pressed when night falls, as long as there are wild animals through, the moment about, volts of high pressure can easily knock out an adult black bear. Qin Gang said the machine is called "electric tiger" , there have been accidental injuries killed incidents. General Forest area of each forestry personnel is about 10,000 acres, at least 10 times a month to patrol the mountain, every day to write a work log. Every mating season in the wild, around March and April, some poachers also carry a lure that fires a simulated female pheromone at the males, luring them into a net.

There must be "brave men" under the heavy reward. According to people familiar with the situation, black market transactions can not only be bought and sold on the spot. Some buyers pay high prices and assign animals to pay a deposit. Some stalls are nearby farmers who "live off the land, live off the water, and live off the mountains. " Some large scale traders have their own network of channels for buying game that is not available locally: a wild weasel costs 2,000 yuan, a peacock costs more than 800 yuan, deer tendons, tiger bones, wolf's tooth Fox skin, and wild animals are disassembled and sorted on the black market, there's a price tag for life and death.

The state's second-class protected animal, the Pangolin, is known as a "treasure all over the body" , with Scales and meat used as medicine. In March last year, Chinese and Vietnamese customs jointly seized 8.25 tons of Pangolin scales from a container declared as imported plastic pellets in Haiphong, meaning about 16,000 pangolins were killed.

Some people believe in folk remedies, such as "the heart of a Hedgehog can cure heart disease" and "the penis of a stag can enhance virility" . According to people familiar with the matter, bear oil on the black market has always been "the best medicine for Rheumatic Diseases" , it is said that you can cure a disease by spreading oil on it and baking it over a fire. "Black bears are the most valuable in autumn and winter. They are fattened up and can be sold for their paws, bear meat and bear oil. "

Others are "willing to die" . According to a Dongting Lake Fisheries official, illegal fishing continues unabated, with the Yangtze swordfish selling for more than 1,000 yuan a piece at its highest, some people risk violating the criminal law by killing and trading the finless porpoise, a second-class national protected animal. Others want to try the high-priced meat of the porpoise, "a mouthful of the puffer fish is tasteless. " Last May, a fisherman in the town of Pudong Academy of classical learning sold two wild puffer fish to a chef who claimed to be an "old hand" and died of poisoning after eating them. As the body contains highly toxic neurotoxins, the relevant regulations of the Ministry of Health clearly stipulated that puffer fish can not enter the market, and prohibit the supply of puffer fish and its salted products.

Working in the forestry sector for more than 20 years, Masked palm civet is one of Qin Gang's most impressive wildlife. During the SARS period, in January 2004, Guangdong issued a "civet cat hunting order" , killing all civet cats within 5 days, no matter alive, dead, raw and cooked, must be immediately sealed and destroyed. "At that time, we were being investigated as if we had seen a plague. "

Qin Gang had also confiscated a pair of bear paws, "hairy, shorter and wider than a person's arms and legs, " Qin Gang said, adding that restaurants typically steamed braised meat in special freezers for regulars and sold the paws for more than $10,000.

One of the main sources of support for foresters is the dark line villagers, who know the whereabouts of poaching families and can report clues. The ranger station is the first inspection down the mountain, someone carrying an animal down the mountain, Qin Gang often pretended to be the buyer and asked: "How can you prove that this is the meat of the MUNTJAC? " The other side of the bag leaked out a corner, the unique white hairs of the wrist exposed, after confirmation, qin just identified himself. Some farmers who did not understand the wildlife protection law were found to have three kinds of wild animal meat in their freezers. The Poacher's wife drank the pesticide and said, "if you arrest someone, I will die! " Qin Gang had to take her to the hospital.

Village traffic is blocked, many farmers do not directly contact the black market, there are "two dealers" to buy on a regular basis, the price fluctuations are very large. MUNTJAC meat to yellow Muntjac the most expensive, when in short supply to more than 100 a catty, but the resale price on the black market can be doubled. When we get to the restaurant, we can double or triple the price. Local restaurants could identify the inspectors, and Qin Gang and his men raided the freezers, but sometimes the wildlife was moved so quickly that many people hid in the trunks of private cars. "You can only check one car at a time, " Qin Gang said, noting that civet cats were the focus of inspections during SARS, all poultry procedures were checked again and again during bird flu, and four checkpoints were set up in county towns during swine fever in Africa. But helpless is, "check more strict game sell the price is higher, more people buy. "

Qin Gang also did not expect, over the mountains, neighbouring Shiyan province, a county, wild animal meat "like Chinese cabbage to sell. ". A few years ago, he went to the local ordinary vegetable market, found in Shaanxi repeated strict investigation of the MUNTJAC meat blatantly appeared on the chopping board, there are many other game. "It also belongs to the Qinba Mountain area, the wild animals are alive, today in Shaanxi, tomorrow may run to Hubei, where we treat them as if they were our own children, how could they have become dinner on other people's plates in the past? " recalled, qin Gang was still frustrated, and when he got back, he reported back to his superiors, hoping for interprovincial communication.

Civets, the intermediate host of SARS virus in humans. Image courtesy of the web

The Angel of death

Life and death, health and illness, hope and despair, these may be only a thin line between venison, as long as the slaughter is improper, greedy chopsticks, contact with an infected wild animal, the human condition may have entered the post-florida stage -- in the eyes of medical experts, some wild animals have another name: hosts, organisms that provide a home for parasites, viruses, and so on.

In 2013, an international team led by Shi Zhengli, a researcher at the Chinese Academy of Sciences, isolated a SARS-like coronavirus that was highly homologous to the SARS virus, according to media reports, studies of the virus's functional receptors and infection have shown that Chinese rufous horseshoe bat is the natural host of the SARS virus, which is transmitted to humans through an intermediate host, civets.

The bat-related cases are not unique. As of December 2,2014, the World Health Organization's report on the Ebola outbreak, according to public information, was released after a massive outbreak of Zaire ebolavirus in West Africa began in February 2014, guinea, Liberia, Sierra Leone, Mali, the United States, as well as Nigeria, Senegal, and Spain, where the outbreak has ended, have a cumulative total of 17,290 confirmed, suspected, and probable cases of Ebola, including 6,128 deaths. According to multiple foreign media reports, the outbreak may have originated from a 2 year old child who died in Guinea after being bitten by a fruit bat infected with Zaire ebolavirus. In her public speeches, she has spoken of two serious epidemics in the 1990s: an outbreak of Hendra Setiawan virus in Australia, which passed from Horse to human; and an outbreak of Nipah virus in Malaysia, which passed from pig to human. The data show that the scientists found that the natural host of the two viruses are fruit bats.

A paper published in the Chinese Journal of Zoonotic Diseases said the link between bats and coronaviruses is a worldwide phenomenon, it is the reservoir of many human viruses, including rabies, Marburg virus, Nipah, and Hendra Setiawan. The Bat's ability to infect a variety of viruses and transmit them to other animals, including humans, is determined by its biological and ecological characteristics.

Shi explained the spread of Nipah virus in his speech: The rapid expansion of human activity into wildlife habitats. We built the pig farm next to the Bat Habitat, and the bat ate the fruit, and the fruit was contaminated by the virus and fell into the pen, and the pigs ate it and got sick and then infected people again.

She stressed: "whether it is the eating of wild animals, or the erosion of Wildlife Habitat, which has led to a significant increase in human contact with animals, creating the conditions for the spread of the virus from wild animals to humans. ". Coupled with the rapid development of globalization and convenient means of transportation, infectious diseases can soon spread from a small village to the world."

Even if bats in the eyes of doctors as the Messenger of death, but in the eyes of some Venison Diners "tonic medicine is better than tonic" , dare to try bat meat is not in the minority. "It feels as tender as chicken, " A lanky internet sensation with a long nose shared on social media. Bats are not uncommon on the black market. In a southern seafood market, dozens of dead bats were stacked on a wooden board. The butcher was quick to chop off two wings, slice open the abdomen and gut the animals. He could pack one in less than a minute. But a regular buyer of bat meat explained that it was difficult to preserve, and that in the summer the stench was so great that the flies could smell far away. "You have to know how to make it. Good Soup is fresh. Meat tastes like plastic if you don't make it right. " More people shared the bat soup on social media, where the whole bat was cooked and its body hair preserved.

The net friend displays the bat health soup. The picture comes from the network

Bats and civet cats are not the only hosts that have tangled with human fate. In September 2012, a sixth human-known coronavirus, called Mers, was discovered in Saudi Arabia, as of June 1,2015, according to media reports, more than 1,000 of the 1,054 MERS cases worldwide have come from Saudi Arabia. But according to The Lancet, a leading journal of Integrative Medicine, camels may be one of the main hosts. According to public information, camel milk is an important source of nutrition in some Middle Eastern countries, and in some areas camel urine is believed to be a cure.

In the round after round of directly to the game of the epidemic crisis, the game did not disappear, the identity of the host was forgotten. Seventeen years after the SARS epidemic, and years ago this year, some game markets had already put up premium signs. According to Qin Gang, the big civet cat weighed 13 to 14 pounds, which rose to more than 200 pounds in December. In the seafood markets of Hubei and Guangdong, wild bamboo rats are very popular in restaurants, with game items such as Sika deer, banded Krait and Wolf pups coming on the market, restaurant owner Xu Shu said: "game stress a 'wild' , the boss of experience to buy a look at the stock know is not breeding. "

Butterfly Wings

It all came to an abrupt end in the face of the Wuhan epidemic. Since December 2019, many cases of viral pneumonia have been reported in Wuhan, and on January 12,2020, the World Health Organization officially named the COVID-19 that caused the outbreak of pneumonia in Wuhan as "COVID-192019" . Zhong Nanshan, a senior expert at the COVID-19, analyzed the outbreak and concluded that there was a human to human transmission of the pneumonia, which may have originated in wild animals such as bamboo rats and badgers, COVID-19 said on Jan. 22, at a news conference held by the State Council Information Office, Takatomi, director of the COVID-19, said the animals came from the illegal sale of wild animals at a Wuhan Seafood Market.

As of 15:20 on January 25, media reports showed that the national confirmed number of the epidemic of 1,346 cases, suspected cases of 1,965 cases, 41 deaths. Bats and minks may be potential hosts for COVID-19, according to a study published on Jan. 24 by Zhu Huaiqiu, a professor in the Department of Biomedical Engineering at Peking University's Engineering School, Beijing News reported, the mink may be the intermediate host.

After the outbreak, some netizens had tried to search Wuhan's venison restaurants on the food software, but found that only input "flavor" to find a few scattered. Feng Jingrun, a Wuhan native born in the 1990s, rented an office near the Hankou Railway Station after graduating from college, just outside the South China seafood market where the outbreak began. "They also sell wild animals, which are sold wholesale to restaurants, " said Feng, who only once walked in when he passed in the summer and was greeted by foul water and a fishy smell. "We don't eat the game because we don't want to get sick, " Feng said, a roommate in the south once ate a bobcat out of curiosity, but told him, "it's not good, the meat is sour. ".

He had planned to spend the New Year's Eve with his parents and ordered a New Year's Eve dinner at a hot pot restaurant, but as the epidemic spread, the dinner was quickly canceled. The Wuhan Epidemic Prevention and Control Headquarters announced at 2:00 a.m. on January 23,2020, the city's bus, subway, ferry and long-distance passenger services were suspended from 10:00 a.m. on January 23,2020, airports and railway stations are temporarily closed from the Han corridor. Recovery time will be announced later.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Commodity Price List of Venison shop in south China Seafood Market. Image courtesy of the web

The South China Seafood Market, the source of the outbreak, has remained closed since it closed on January 1. According to media reports, the market has recently started to return shops to pay rent in advance, the local government has also started to distribute living allowances to merchants. On September 25,2019, the Wuhan Market Supervision Authority announced that on the morning of the same day, the two-level urban market supervision departments, together with the municipal forestry and forest public security departments, launched a special operation to regulate the wild animal market, in the South China Seafood Wholesale Market, law enforcement officers at the two levels in the urban areas conducted a carpet inspection of nearly eight businesses selling animals such as tiger frogs, snakes and hedgehogs, and checked their wildlife business license approval documents and business licenses one by one, the management of unapproved wild animals shall be strictly prohibited.

"game pneumonia" quickly became a trending topic on Weibo, with 460 million views. Netizens quarreled under a news report, with some insisting: "It's Ok for me to eat wild food for more than 20 years? The problem isn't eating, it's health control. " A boy who just returned to his hometown in southern China for the New Year is working in the car service industry, holding a piece of fresh ginger meat in his hand, he took a picture: The wild fruit civet from the mountain, just delivered by his cousin, was stewed tonight; in Shunchang County of Nanping, Fujian Province, a family's mouse dry new year goods were ready; in a third-tier city in northeast China, ms. Li, who works in the precision instrument industry, said her family's New Year's Eve dinner, "a hard dish, " was made of wild Roe deer meat and "stewed with pickled cabbage. "

In the entertainment around game, medicinal wine is still a "top-grade thing" for business gifts. Lin Jianan, a native of Zhejiang province, gave medicinal wine soaked with snakes, centipedes, ants, deer penis and so on, with similar efficacy, "It's good. " But he never drinks it himself. Four or five years ago, he received a Taiwanese customer, who wanted to bring some mainland specialties, finally chose tiger penis wine, said to have aphrodisiac effect. After returning to Taiwan, the clients invited guests. Each of the dozen or so guests gave only a small cup of wine, and friends who had tasted the wine praised the effect. After the wine was drunk, the family felt that "the tiger penis can not be wasted" and wanted to stew the soup, which was too hard for an ordinary knife to separate, i had to ask a special master to do it. "IT TURNED OUT TO BE RUBBER! "
